DelayMode: What mode to set the stereo delay effect.
DelayTimeMsec: The base amount of delay in the left and right channels of the delay line.
Feedback: The amount of audio to feedback into the delay line once the delay has been tapped.
DelayRatio: Delay spread for left and right channels. Allows left and right channels to have differential delay amounts. Useful for stereo channel decorrelation.
WetLevel: The amount of delay effect to mix with the dry input signal into the effect.
DryLevel: The dry level of the effect
bFilterEnabled: Whether or not to enable filtering
FilterType: Filter type to feed feedback audio to
